): HL (0.88–0.94); HW (0.84–0.90); ML (0.57–0.60); SL (0.62–0.66); MOD (0.20–0.24); PNW (0.56–0.64); WL (1.14–1.24); PSL (0.16–0.19); PL (0.52–0.59); PW (0.20–0.22); PPL (0.32–0.34); PPW (0.30–0.31); GL (0.98–1.02); TL (4.41–4.71); CI (94.44–96.62); SI (73.33–76.47); OI (23.81– 26.66). Small-sized. Shiny integument. Brownish body, darker gaster, lighter appendices. Thin and branched setae (
